column3:
QUESTION ONE  
In relation to company law distinguish between:  
a) executive directors;  
b) non‐executive directors;  
c) shadow directors.

QUESTION THREE  
In relation to the rules governing the payment of company dividends explain:  
a) how dividends may be properly funded;  
b) the rules which apply to public limited companies;  
c) the consequences of any dividend being paid in breach of those rules.

QUESTION FOUR  
Within the context of the UN Convention on Contracts for the International Sale of Goods, explain:  
(a) an offer;  
(b) an invitation to treat;  
(c) a counter‐offer.
